edge: Anand Kumar, played by Hrithik Roshan, founded Super 30 to help 30 poor students prepare for JEE Advanced examinations
Anand Kumar, played by Hrithik Roshan, has a romantic relationship with Supriya Singh, portrayed by Mrunal Thakur
Virendra Saxena played the role of Rajendra Prasad Kumar, Anand and Pranav's father who dies from a heart attack after Anand misses an opportunity to join Cambridge University due to poverty
Pranav Kumar, played by Nandish Sandhu, is Anand's younger brother who supports him in his work
Aditya Srivastava portrayed the character of Lallan Singh, Shriram's evil assistant who used education only as a means of business
Sadhana Singh played the role of Jayanti Kumar, Anand and Pranav's hardworking mother
Pankaj Tripathi acted as Shriram Singh, the local minister
Vijay Varma played the character of Fugga Kumar, one of Anand's students who narrates his teacher's story as a successful man in London
Amit Sadh acted as Raghunath Bharat, a reporter
Anud Singh Dhaka portrayed the role of Raghunath's assistant
Sharat Sonu acted as Haadim Malik, Shriram's secretary
Manav Gohil played the role of IAS Purushottam Singh, Supriya's husband
Aayush Kumar Shukla portrayed the character of Vinod
Rajesh Sharma played the role of Bachchi
Vivek Jha acted as a villager
Krithi Shetty portrayed the character of a student from an excellence coaching center
